            <small id="caption">
               Vijay, often referred to as Thalapathy Vijay, is a popular Indian actor and playback singer who predominantly works in the Tamil film industry. He was born as Joseph Vijay Chandrasekhar on June 22, 1974, in Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India. Vijay is one of the most successful and influential actors in the South Indian film industry.
            </small>
        </div>
 
        <div id="tribute-data">
 
           
            <h1 class="title-VJ">
                About the Ilayathalapthy 
            </h1>
            <p> &#10054; Vijay comes from a film background, as his father, S. A. Chandrasekhar, is a well-known Tamil film director, and his mother, Shoba Chandrasekhar, is a playback singer.<br> <br>&#10054;From a young age, Vijay showed a keen interest in acting and performed in minor roles as a child artist in his father’s films.<br><br> &#10054;Vijay made his debut as a lead actor in the film “Naalaiya Theerpu” in 1992, directed by his father. However, it was his breakthrough role in the film “Poove Unakkaga” (1996) that brought him recognition and established him as a bankable star. <br><br>&#10054;Some of Vijay’s notable films include “Ghilli” (2004), “Thuppakki” (2012), “Mersal” (2017), and “Master” (2021).<br><br>&#10054;In 2010, he acted in the action comedy film Sura, which was his 50th film as an actor.<br><br>&#10054;Vijay was awarded the Best International Actor of 2018 in the United Kingdom for his role in Mersal.<br><br>&#10054;His upcoming sci-fi film The Greatest of All Time which is set to be released theatrically on 5 September 2024.<br><br>&#10054;In February 2024, Vijay announced that he will be doing only one more film, which will be his 69th as a lead actor.<br><br>&#10054;Vijay, through his fan club Thalapathy Vijay Makkal Iyakkam (TVMI), distributed relief materials, including essential commodities for a few hundred families from Tirunelveli and Thoothukudi districts, and the crowd gathering went out of control, injuring half a dozen people who had thronged the venue
</p>
